## Recurrence protection

These disciplines compound per `16-architectural-inheritance.mdc`
§"Continuous discipline as inheritance prevention." Citing this
file in design-round 1+ plan-docs replaces re-reading
`RANDOMX_V2_PHASE2C_PLAN.md` round history for **process** shape;
cite the 2c plan-doc only for RandomX-specific substrate.

When a reviewer sees a violation (uncited audit row, test-only `pub`
widener, scope move without reversion clause), reject per
`15-deletion-and-debt.mdc` scope discipline — fix the process
artifact, not the implementation in the same PR if that PR's scope
is unrelated.

